Hey, Ryan.

00:44.634 --> 00:45.954
What time is it?

00:45.994 --> 00:48.154
Eh, it's 5:30... ish.

00:48.234 --> 00:49.834
Showing up
earlier and earlier.

00:49.914 --> 00:52.194
Yeah, well, we have a
lot of ground to cover,

00:52.274 --> 00:54.034
so I figured,
since we're both up,

00:54.114 --> 00:55.714
we may as well
get a jump on it.

00:55.754 --> 00:57.554
Yeah, I know.
We've been over this.

00:57.634 --> 00:59.754
Summer doesn't want you,
she doesn't want Zach--

00:59.794 --> 01:00.994
all there is to it.

01:01.074 --> 01:03.994
Good night.

01:04.034 --> 01:05.594
But something
occurred to me--

01:05.674 --> 01:06.714
a new wrinkle.

01:06.754 --> 01:07.954
What, the prom?
Yeah.

01:07.994 --> 01:09.994
And I have to convince Summer
to go with me.

01:10.074 --> 01:11.514
We-- as a couple, Ryan--

01:11.554 --> 01:15.194
must partake in the magical rite
of passage known as "the prom."

01:15.274 --> 01:17.594
Ah, you mean people
getting drunk, making out,

01:17.634 --> 01:19.074
throwing up
on the gym floor?

01:19.114 --> 01:20.474
No, I mean
romance, Ryan.

01:20.554 --> 01:23.674
I mean tuxedos, corsages,
the limousines.

01:23.714 --> 01:25.074
I don't know, man,
I don't see Summer

01:25.114 --> 01:26.474
really buying in
to the prom thing.

01:26.514 --> 01:28.554
You're wrong about that--
Summer's been fantasizing

01:28.594 --> 01:29.794
about prom since fifth grade.

01:29.874 --> 01:31.194
How do you know that?

01:31.234 --> 01:33.154
Sat behind her and Marissa
in computer class.

01:33.194 --> 01:35.234
Really honed my eavesdropping
skills that year.

01:35.274 --> 01:36.994
Point is, Summer's

01:37.074 --> 01:38.914
forever dreamt of
going to the prom,

01:38.954 --> 01:41.394
and I, in turn, would
dream of going with her.

01:41.474 --> 01:43.314
Well, you need to get that
out of your mind.

01:43.394 --> 01:45.754
If it helps at all,
I don't think I'm
gonna go, either.

01:45.834 --> 01:47.714
Look, just 'cause you saw Trey
leaving Marissa's

01:47.754 --> 01:48.994
does not mean
they're hooking up.

01:49.034 --> 01:50.754
Yeah? What does it mean?

01:50.834 --> 01:53.194
Maybe he went over to borrow
something, like a book.

01:53.274 --> 01:54.714
Or one of her
newsboy caps.

01:54.794 --> 01:56.194
Yeah, or maybe they hooked up.

01:56.274 --> 01:58.434
Okay, you're just... married

01:58.474 --> 02:00.074
to the worst possible
scenario, huh?

02:00.154 --> 02:02.354
Look, I'm gonna talk to her
about it today,

02:02.434 --> 02:05.354
but whatever happened, she seems
dead set on keeping it from me.

02:07.074 --> 02:09.114
It's kind of early
for a phone call.

02:09.193 --> 02:11.434
Kind of early
for a lot of things.
Hello?

02:11.474 --> 02:14.714
Dad? Where...
where are you?

02:17.034 --> 02:19.194
Oh, my God.

02:19.234 --> 02:21.474
Okay. Uh, yeah.

02:21.554 --> 02:23.874
We'll be
right there.
What is it?

02:23.954 --> 02:26.194
My mom got in a car accident--
she's at the hospital.

